-- Polish bank Alior confirms Carlo Tassara sold stake at PLN 79/shr
-- 
-- Fri Apr 25, 2014 08:57AM EDT
-- None



WARSAW, April 25 (Reuters) - The Carlo Tassara Group has sold a 4.7 percent stake in Poland's mid-tier bank Alior Bank <ALRR.WA> at 79 zlotys per share, the bank confirmed on Friday.

On Wednesday, market sources told Reuters that Carlo Tassara found buyers for a stake valued at almost 261 million zlotys ($86 million). [ID:nW8N0MZ00P] Carlo Tassara, the holding company for French financier Romain Zaleski, controlled 32.77 percent of Alior before it sold the stake.